Here is a clean, modern, industry-ready naming convention guide you can follow for GitHub folders, documentation files, backend Java/Spring Boot code, frontend React code, and API naming.
This is the same style used by big companies (Google, Meta, Stripe, Airbnb, Netflix).

âœ… 1. General Folder Naming Conventions (GitHub Repo)
Best Practices

âœ” Use lowercase
âœ” Use hyphens (-) instead of underscores or spaces
âœ” Do NOT prefix with numbers unless ordering matters
âœ” Keep names semantic, short, and consistent

âŒ Avoid

01_folder_name/

Backend_Project/

My Files/

camelCaseFolder

âœ… Do

backend/

frontend/

api-specs/

system-design/

uml-diagrams/

ğŸ’¡ Why hyphens?

Hyphens are most universal â€” compatible with Linux, URLs, npm, Java packages, and CLI tools.

âœ… 2. Documentation File Naming Conventions
Best practices:

âœ” Keep filenames lowercase-with-hyphens
âœ” Use .md for all documentation
âœ” Include a clear topic name

Examples:
README.md
