âœ… 5. API Naming Conventions (REST)
Endpoints

âœ” lower-case
âœ” hyphens in URL
âœ” nouns, not verbs
âœ” versioned

Example:
/api/v1/users
/api/v1/users/{id}
/api/v1/auth/login
/api/v1/ai/generate
/api/v1/security/scan

Response fields

âœ” snake_case (industry standard for APIs)
OR camelCase (if frontend prefers it)

Pick one and stay consistent.

â­ Recommended Style for You (Clean & Professional)
For folders:

lowercase-with-hyphens

For JS/React files:

PascalCase for components, camelCase for helpers

For Java files:

PascalCase for classes, camelCase for methods

For APIs:

lowercase-hyphens + versioning: /api/v1/...

For documentation:

